subSubSection.paragraph:
Female genitalia (fig. 
48
). Segment VIII ventrally with crescent­shaped lamella postvaginalis, microtrichia and a shallow median invagination. Distal end of the ventral groove marked by a small sclerotized extension. Dorsal side of segment VIII without a median tongue. Signum large, about twice as long as wide, strongly tapering toward the distal end, with stout spikes on the corners and a clear pointed extension distal to the last spikes. Easily recognized by the shape of the signum in combination with the distal end of the ventral groove.
